Hi!

The Academic Affairs Sub-committee of the Student Legislative Council has
been ideating on improving the choice of free elective available to
students and has come up with a list of courses Co-curricular and Cultural
Activities that can be added as free electives. This initiative is in line
with the Curriculum Task Force report that was approved by the Senate in
which emphasis was placed on allowing students to take nearly 50% of
courses from any department of their choice.

The free electives that the committee is looking at right now are -

1. Introduction to Fashion Technology
2. Embedded Coding
3. Introduction to Photography
4. Agriculture: Theory and Practice
5. Introduction to Film Making

Please fill this <https://goo.gl/forms/3q8SffM54N88qicF2> form before the
5th of August to let us know your preference. You can give your suggestions
in the form too.

Cheers!
Venkataraman


